Scripts for running NCBI Blastp
===============================

+ Downloading blastp:
  + see http://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/IEB/ToolBox/CPP_DOC

+ Scripts configuration
  + scripts are in the scripts directory
  + you need to configure blastp_source according to your local installation of blastp and databases
  + you need to configure blastp_generic.sh according to the installation of blastp_source
  + you can use testBlastp.sh to test the script, just check its configuration
  
+ Examples
  + two input .fasta files are provided in the examples directory
  + input.fasta only contains one short sequence
  + input2.fasta only contains one long sequence
  + input3.fasta contains 20 short sequences

+ Databases
  + you need to configure the .pal files in your database installation


+ For the webboard:
 + add an application with the following parameters (name, label (type, format)):
   - blastp_used_db, Database (string, select[Default])
   - query_file, Input file (string, file)
   - blastp_evalue, eValue (double, textField)
   - blastp_outfmt, outfmt (integer, textField)
